      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:1:1:1:6",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) مَنْ كَانَ عَاقِلًا كَانَ لَهُ دِينٌ وَ مَنْ كَانَ لَهُ دِينٌ دَخَلَ الْجَنَّةَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ahmad Bin Idrees, from Muhammad Bin Hassan, from Abu Muhammad Al Razy, from Sayf Bin Ameyra, from Is’haq Bin Ammar who said, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘The one who was an intellectual, there would be Religion for him, and the one who has Religion for him, would enter the Paradise’."
        ]
      }
    }
